<dl id="n25188b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n25" href="#n25188b">N25 (VI.B.15)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n25all.htm#n25188b"> 188(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> limitor / (beggar</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[Langland]</font> speaks of the four orders of monks, of their wealth and political power, their greed, their hypocrisy, their sins, and their intrusion into houses and family life. He describes the pardoner with his bulls, the <mark>limitor licensed to beg</mark> within certain limits <small> Claude R. Conder, <a name="CRRM" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#CRRM"><cite title="source">The Rise of Man</cite></a> (1908) 340</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c14128d" href="c14all.htm#c14128d">VI.C.14:128(d)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
